==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pumice
<hw>Pum"ice</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>pumex</ets>,
<ets>pumicis</ets>, prob. akin to <ets>spuma</ets> foam: cf. AS.
<ets>pumic-</ets>st⟦amac⟧n. Cf. <er>Pounce</er> a powder,
<er>Spume</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A very light porous
volcanic scoria, usually of a gray color, the pores of which are
capillary and parallel, giving it a fibrous structure. It is supposed to
be produced by the disengagement of watery vapor without liquid or
plastic lava. It is much used, esp. in the form of powder, for smoothing
and polishing. Called also <altname>pumice stone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pumiced</ent>⟦br⟧
